{"key":"post-9243219","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9243219</id>\n<content>If you have the terrarium near a bright window, it's going to be fine for light.&amp;nbsp; If it's away from a window, use fluorescent lights.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Treat uncased substrate like a cake.&amp;nbsp; Mist several times per day, and always fan out well right afterwards.&amp;nbsp; You can and should mist even after pins form, but just be sure to provide plenty of fresh air.&amp;nbsp; The old advice to 'not mist after primordia form' was from the era of totally closed up terrariums, where a wet substrate would easily mold in the stale air.&amp;nbsp; With the shotgun-type terrarium you're using, you should mist right through to a few hours before harvest.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9243631</next>\n<prev>9242996</prev>\n<first>9242923</first>\n<last>9247781</last>\n<when>1226682566</when>\n<utime>11/14/08 07:09 PM</utime>\n</post>"}